Title: 2 Honda Monkey Bikes 2021, 2022
text: 2021 Honda Monkey Bike in like new, stock condition, 4 speed, 415-ish miles. Clean and clear title, street legal. We purchased 2 to take on RV trips, but my wife is just not super comfortable riding.   Firm on price,iIn Sonora 95370. Need to sell not trade.   If the add is the up, the bike is available.

Title: ELECTRIC! The Mid-drive eBike that Shreds! CyberBike eMountain Bikes!
text: Introducing the New 2022 Cyberbike Electric Mountain Bikes   Riders agree: Nothing comes close to Cyberbike's combination of performance, value, style, and quality.  See the Cyberbike Mullet Pro in action HERE! (and here, by popular demand, is last year's intro featuring Division 1 Collegiate Mountain Racer Corey Jackson on the first edition Cyberbike) Order online for fast delivery at www.Cyberbike.com All 2022 Cyberbikes are in stock and ready to shred, Order yours before they're sold out!  More mid-drive power than ever Awesome new color graphic display Easier to ride, lower standover frame, the lowest of any mid-drive eMTB New, structurally superior, mountain ready rear suspension linkage The best brakes in the business, even Quad-piston brakes on some models! Massive brake rotors up to 220mm 34mm gold tube forks on some models up to 140mm travel Wider range of models  A proper e-Mountain bike needs to be mid-drive and have full suspension, it's as simple as that. Until now, if you wanted an electric mountain bike to tackle rugged trails, your choices have been heavy, low-quality, fat tire, hub-motor beach bikes, or legacy brands charging $4000 or more for low-power eBikes without full suspension.   Whether your knees are tired or you just want to shred, there is simply no better choice for performance and value than Cyberbike. An American company with great customer support: Cyberbike, USA. The mountains are calling. Will you answer?  Cyberbike eBikes come all with the quietest and most powerful motor in its class, with a long range (65 miles and more) battery, and powerful e-spec hydraulic disk brakes that will be there when you need them. A lightweight package with 500 watts of power, top-of-the-line battery range, and quality components, all for the price of an inexpensive yet stellar bike! You'll get so much more than other eBikes with the CyberBike, it's the real e-MTB experience for the adventurous rider. Performance, specs, and quality components throughout, and the best warranty in the industry, from an American company with experienced American mechanics on call for all your tech support needs.  54 volt/500 watt climbing power with 13Amp hour Li-Ion battery and only 52 lbs means you'll get power and tons of battery range. Now with available throttle! Now from only $2495 Note: Owning and riding comes with risks. Wear proper protection, properly maintain and check your bike, and ride within your limits. By purchasing our products you agree to take full responsibility for the ownership of your bike, including the above and all other reasonable precautions for yourself or anyone you allow to ride your bike.

Title: 2 Mountain bikes/His/Hers/ 15 speed
text: 2 Mountain bikes, 26" tires, his/hers, 15speed, good condition, recent tune up on both bikes, new tires on both, new YLG wide seats on female bike(very comfy)  (men's bike has it's stock padded seat ) gears works as they should as well as brakes. both have water bottle holders, handle bar bike bells and all reflectors. Paint is scratched a little bit from hauling on bike rack over the years.....good time to own a bike with the gas price as they are and will be for awhile.....these two are ready to be ridden.... $180 for BOTH bikes ..or best offer....... 209- 6o6-21seven seven.....

Title: 2022 Heartland Milestone 360HP ***HIDDEN ROOM / LIFETIME WARRANTY!**
text: www,referralautogroup.com  Referral Auto Group 1444 First St Escalon, Ca 95320  (209) 404-2200  TOP EXTERIOR FEATURES  2” receiver hitch 20 Watt solar panel with inverter prep Upgraded MORryde solid step with quick adjust system at every door Anti-chucking rotoflex hitch Full profile painted front cap Friction Hinge 30” Entrance Doors Quad Aluminum Steps Massive Tinted Safety Glass Windows for Superior Ventilation Solar Prep and Back-up Camera Prep  TOP INTERIOR FEATURES  14 Cubic foot residential refer with wine cooler (Milestone) 40” Luxury fireplace (most models) Chef kitchen (30” over the range microwave/21? large RV oven) X1 control system 50” Entertainment tv with integrated sound bar Washer/Dryer prep Modern bright farmhouse interiors  CONSTRUCTION STANDARD FEATURES  Full Profile Straight Roofline 6’5” Slideouts 4-5 Slide Floorplans Painted/Clearcoat Front Gelcoat Cap  KITCHEN STANDARD FEATURES  14 Cubic foot residential refer with wine cooler Chef kitchen (30?over the range microwave/21” large RV oven) Anti-Microbial Solid Surface Kitchen Countertops Farm Sink with Stainless Single hole Pull-out Faucet Hardwood Drawers with Full Extension Drawer Guides  HOME OF THE WARRANTY FOREVER!!!  Remember all our inventory is NON AUCTION bought! We have fought the fight in the 7 western states for you to find the cleanest pre-owned RV's and brought them to one spot, HERE!  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ). Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm and closed Sunday & Mondays  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!! WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing! Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video! Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided, IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BUYER TO VERIFY PRIOR TO PURCHASE. Specifications, equipment, technical data, photographs and illustrations subject to change without notice. To verify current product information, please call our sales department. Any prices listed on this site are subject to change without notice and do not include tax and license fees. text: www.referralautogroup.com  Referral Auto Group 1444 First St Escalon, Ca 95320  (209) 404-2200  OPTIONS INCLUDED:  - Power hitch & stabilizer jacks - Solar - Roller shades - Fireplace - Flat screen TV - Upgraded queen mattress   PRODUCT FEATURES  • 2000-lb. Tongue Jack • EZ Lube Axles • 8” Rust Resistant Powder Coated I-Beam Chassis • 4-wheel Electric Self Adjusting Brakes • 15” Radial Trailer Special Tires • 4” Steel Rear Bumper/Sewer Hose Storage w/end caps • Frame Mounted Dual Battery Rack • Schwintec Electric Slide-out Operating System, Flush Floor per Floor Plan • Full through Chassis Electric Slide Room Support System (Super Slides) • One-piece Promax OSB waterproof slide-out floor decking • R-7 Johns Mansville Fiberglass Insulation Roof/Floor/Walls/End Caps • Full Walk-On Roof with One-piece PVC Roofing Membrane • Enclosed Underbelly w/Heat Duct  INTERIOR  • Boutique Craftsmen Cabinets w/Hidden Latches • Brushed Nickle Cabinet Hardware • Wood Drawer Fronts • Deluxe Ball Bearing Drawer Guides • Galley Lighting • System Capacity Monitor Panel • Systems Control Panel • Two 12v/USB Charging Stations at Bunk Area • Extra Large Country Kitchen Sink w/Recessed Covers • Chefs Hi-Rise Sink Faucet • Full Wall Tub/Shower Surround • Glass Enclosure (Showers) • Power Vent in Bathroom • Medicine Cabinet with Mirror • Full Length Bedroom Wardrobes • Denver Mattress • Lift Up Bed for Storage Per. FP • 110V Outlets on both sides of main bed • 48” Storage Drawer under Slide Sofa • Shoe Storage under Entertainment Center • Knife Holder Behind Range • Solid Doors at Bedroom Entry (Per FP) • Laundry Chutes (Per FP)  MANDATORY OPTIONS  • Solid Surface Counter Top w/under Mount Country Sink • Power Stabilizer Jacks • Power Tongue Jack w/Light • Power Awning with Shock Absorbers • LED Light Strip Porch Light • LED Power Saving Interior Lighting • Blue Tooth Stereo with DVD Player AM/FM • Night Shades in Living Area • Solar Prep for Portable Unit • Back-up Camera Prep. • Denver Pillow Top Memory Foam Mattress • Push Button Remote (Operates Slide, Awning, Jacks, Porch Light)  ARCTIC PACKAGE (OPTIONAL)  • Radiant Foil Insulation in Roof and Floor for R-38 equivalent • Fully Enclosed Underbelly with heat duct to tank area  EXTERIOR  • Front Pass-through Storage with LED Light • Crowned Roof for Water Drainage • Black Frame Safety Glass Windows30-amp. 110v Power Cord • Cable TV Hook-up • Exterior LED Utility Porch Light • 110V Exterior Plug • Radius Entry Door with Window • Amber Step Light • Radius Compartment Storage Doors • Entry Assist Handle Main Entry • Dometic Awning w/Retractor Assist Springs • Aerodynamic Aluminum Front Cap • Omni Digital TV Antenna w/Booster • LPG Tank Cover with Easy Access • Exterior Speakers • Extended Rain Gutter Spouts • Front Lower Gravel Guard  APPLIANCES  • Suburban 3-Burner Range with 17” oven w/Stainless Steel Appliance Upgrade • Range Hood with LED Light and Exhaust Fan w/Stainless Steel Appliance Upgrade • Dometic 8-cu.ft. Double Door Stainless Steel Appearance • 6-gal. Suburban Gas/Electric DSI Water Heater w/16-gal/hr. recovery • Microwave w/Carousel Hi-Point Stainless Steel Appearance • Dometic 13,500 BTU Air Conditioning • Floor Ducted Heat per Floor Plan • Suburban 20K or 30K BTU Furnace per Floor Plan • Flush Mounted Speakers in Ceiling • AM/FM/DVD/ Bluetooth Stereo System • Interior/Exterior Speakers  OPTIONS  • Ducted Air Conditioning Roof Vents • 15,000 BTU Quick Cool Air Conditioner • HD LED Television with Mount • Deluxe Aluminum Wheels • 135 W GO Power Solar Charging Package • Jiffy Sofa IPO Lower Bunk (3250) • Outside Kitchen (2990, Std 3250) • Large Storage Door at Bunks (2550/2700, Std 2990) • Two Deluxe Recliners (2460, Std 2600/2790)  COMFORT & CONVENIENCE GROUP (OPTIONAL)  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ).  Open daily 9am - 5pm Tuesday - Saturday  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a "no haggle / no high pressure sales" atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing! Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video!  Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200 and our office hours are Tuesday - Saturday 9am - 5pm, we look forward to meeting you!  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided. Specifications, equipment, technical data, photographs and illustrations subject to change without notice. To verify current product information, please call our sales department. Any prices listed on this site are subject to change without notice and do not include tax and license fees. All units are subject to prior sale.  www.referralautogroup.com     class a rv, class a motorhome, recreational vehicle, rv trailer, rvs, trailers for sale, fifth wheel, 5th wheel, travel trailer, Freedom Express conventional and hybrid travel trailers boast vacuum-bond laminated sidewalls with durable Lami-Lux 1000® fiberglass exteriors backed with Azdel. Title: 2022 Coachmen Freedom Express 246RKS**LIFETIME WARRANTY!!**
text: www.referralautogroup.com  REFERRAL AUTO GROUP  1444 FIRST ST ESCALON, CA 95320  (209) 404-2200  Coachmen Freedom Express Ultra Lite 246RKS Freedom Express Ultra Lite Travel Trailers deliver ultra-lite luxury combined with top selling floorplans in an affordable, value packed travel trailer, designed to be towed by today’s midsize SUVs and half-ton vehicles.  Freedom Express conventional and hybrid travel trailers boast vacuum-bond laminated sidewalls with durable Lami-Lux 1000® fiberglass exteriors backed with Azdel. Available in models from 18’ to 28’, you are sure to find a model that suits your style, whether you are going it alone or taking the whole family.  Features may include:  Interior 81" Interior Ceiling Throughout AM/FM/CD/DVD/Bluetooth Stereo 2 Exterior Speakers, 4 Interior Speakers LED Satellite Ready TV LED Interior Lighting Night Shades Congoleum Designer Carefree Flooring Hidden Hinge Cabinetry Stainless Steel Sink with Sink Covers Microwave Oven with 3 Burners & Glass Top Double Door Refrigerator Utensil Drawer (Some models) 60” x 80” Queen Bed with Residential Bed Spread USB Ports in Master & Bunk Rooms Skylight in Bath & Power Vent Fan Porcelain Toilet Freedom Express Clock RVIA Exterior ¾ Gel Coated Fiberglass Cap with Automotive Glass Windshield Alumicage Construction Vacuum Bonded Walls with Azdel Composite Panels Aluminum Wheels Spare Tire Kit Detachable Power Cord Power Awning with LED Light Strip Tinted Safety Glass Windows Front Diamond Plate E-Z Lube® Axles Spread Axle Design Heated Enclosed Underbelly Full Walk-on Roof One Piece Tufflex PVC Roofing 15 year Warranty Exterior Shower Station Winterize Ready Kit Black Tank Flush Ducted Furnace Ducted Ceiling Air Conditioning Magnetic Compartment Door with LED Strip Light 24”x 48” Resin Outdoor Table TV & Radio Antenna with Winegard 360+ WIFI & 4G Prep RG6 TV Hook-up Camp Side Solar Port Back-up Camera Prep Battery Disconnect Aluminum Solid Steps Pet Leash & Bottle Opener by Entry Door     HOME OF THE WARRANTY FOREVER!!!  Remember all our inventory is NON AUCTION bought! We have fought the fight in the 7 western states for you to find the cleanest pre-owned RV's and brought them to one spot, HERE!  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ).  Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!! WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing! Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video! Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200 and our office hours are Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm, we look forward to meeting you!  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided, IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BUYER TO VERIFY PRIOR TO PURCHASE. Specifications, equipment, technical data, photographs and illustrations subject to change without notice. To verify current product information, please call our sales department. Any prices listed on this site are subject to change without notice and do not include tax and license fees. Double layered AZDEL sidewalls • Full extension Drawer guides • Stainless Steel Deep Basin Sink • Large Fiberglass Shower w/ Skylight • Friction Hinge Entry Door w/ MORryde Entry Steps • Quick Recovery Water Heater • Solar, Satellite, and Backup Camera Prep • Dual Ducted A/C for 2nd A/C Option • Fuel Station w/ Generator Prep • Optional Ramp Door Patio w/ Quick Connect Patio System  Standard Features Gravity "Mission" Package: • Solid Stained Hardwood Doors & Drawers • LED Interior Lighting • Drawers with Full Extension Drawer Guides • Stainless Steel Kitchen Sink with Residential Style Faucet • Microwave • 8 Cu. Stainless Steel Refrigerator • 15K BTU Ducted A/C System • 2nd A/C Prep • 8 Gal DSI 110/12V Water Heater with Bypass • Large Shower with Skylight • Toilet with Foot Flush • Queen Bed • Cold Crack Resistant Floor • Cable TV & Satellite Prep • DVD/CD/Radio Entertainment Package • Pleated Night Shades • Quad Aluminum Entry Steps • Power Bed with Convertible Sofa • Reclining Sofa Seating with Fold Down Counsel Featuring Cup Holders & USB Gravity "Apollo" Package: • Wide Body Construction • High Gloss • Aluminum Framed & Laminated Sidewalls • Tinted Safety Glass Windows • Aluminum Rims • Spare Tire • Dexter 7000# Axles • Power Front Landing Gear • Power Rear Stabilizers • Universal Docking Station with Black Tank Flush • Heated & Enclosed Underbelly • LED Stop/Turn/Tail Lights • Twin 30# LP Tanks • Exterior Speakers • Back-up Camera Prep • Power Awning with LED Light • Solar Prep • Triple Entry Garage Steps • Fuel Station with Gen Prep • Rear Ramp Door Options: • 5.5 Onan Gas Generator • Ramp Door Patio With Quick Connect Patio System • 50' Living Room TV • Electric 6 Point Leveling • 2nd 13.5K BTU Air Conditioner  Unmatched Quality Control! At Heartland, we do our absolute best to provide the best to our customers at every turn. We have integrated comprehensive testing and quality control standards throughout the production process. With our new audit facility, we're taking yet another step to ensure that your new RV is ready for camping when you tow it off the dealer lot. We also gather customer feedback through shows, plant tours, phone calls, e-mails, owners forum, rallies and letters. Heartland RV's goal is to set the standard in quality.  HOME OF THE WARRANTY FOREVER!!!  Remember all our inventory is NON AUCTION bought! We have fought the fight in the 7 western states for you to find the cleanest pre-owned RV's and brought them to one spot, HERE!  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ).  Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!! WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing! Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video! Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200 and our office hours are Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm, we look forward to meeting you!  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided, IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BUYER TO VERIFY PRIOR TO PURCHASE. Title: 2022 Freedom Express 275BHS**SOLAR & LIFETIME WARRANTY**
text: WWW.REFERRALAUTOGROUP.COM  REFERRAL AUTO GROUP  1444 FIRST ST ESCALON, CA 95320  (209) 404-2200  Coachmen Freedom Express Ultra Lite 252RBS  Freedom Express Ultra Lite Travel Trailers deliver ultra-lite luxury combined with top selling floorplans in an affordable, value packed travel trailer, designed to be towed by today’s midsize SUVs and half-ton vehicles.  Freedom Express conventional and hybrid travel trailers boast vacuum-bond laminated sidewalls with durable Lami-Lux 1000® fiberglass exteriors backed with Azdel. Available in models from 18’ to 28’, you are sure to find a model that suits your style, whether you are going it alone or taking the whole family.  Features may include:  Interior 81” Interior Ceiling Throughout AM/FM/CD/DVD/Bluetooth Stereo 2 Exterior Speakers, 4 Interior Speakers LED Satellite Ready TV LED Interior Lighting Night Shades Congoleum Designer Carefree Flooring Hidden Hinge Cabinetry Stainless Steel Sink with Sink Covers Microwave Oven with 3 Burners & Glass Top Double Door Refrigerator 60” x 80” Queen Bed with Residential Bed Spread USB Ports in Master & Bunk Rooms Skylight in Bath & Power Vent Fan Porcelain Toilet Freedom Express Clock RVIA Exterior ¾ Gel Coated Fiberglass Cap with Automotive Glass Windshield Alumicage Construction Vacuum Bonded Walls with Azdel Composite Panels Aluminum Wheels Spare Tire Kit Detachable Power Cord Power Awning with LED Light Strip Tinted Safety Glass Windows Front Diamond Plate E-Z Lube® Axles Spread Axle Design Heated Enclosed Underbelly Full Walk-on Roof One Piece Tufflex PVC Roofing 15 year Warranty Exterior Shower Station Winterize Ready Kit Black Tank Flush Ducted Furnace Ducted Ceiling Air Conditioning Magnetic Compartment Door with LED Strip Light 24”x 48” Resin Outdoor Table TV & Radio Antenna with Winegard 360+ WIFI & 4G Prep RG6 TV Hook-up Camp Side Solar Port Back-up Camera Prep Battery Disconnect Aluminum Solid Steps Pet Leash & Bottle Opener by Entry Door  HOME OF THE WARRANTY FOREVER!!!  Remember all our inventory is NON AUCTION bought! We have fought the fight in the 7 western states for you to find the cleanest pre-owned RV's and brought them to one spot, HERE!  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ). Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm and closed Sunday & Mondays  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!! WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing! Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video! Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided, IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BUYER TO VERIFY PRIOR TO PURCHASE. Specifications, equipment, technical data, photographs and illustrations subject to change without notice. To verify current product information, please call our sales department. Any prices listed on this site are subject to change without notice and do not include tax and license fees. All units are subject to prior sale.  www.referralautogroup.com     class a rv, class a motorhome, recreational vehicle, rv trailer, rvs, trailers for sale, fifth wheel, 5th wheel, travel trailer, Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ). Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm and closed Sunday & Mondays  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!! WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us! FP • 110V Outlets on both sides of main bed • 48” Storage Drawer under Slide Sofa • Shoe Storage under Entertainment Center • Knife Holder Behind Range • Solid Doors at Bedroom Entry (Per FP) • Laundry Chutes (Per FP)  MANDATORY OPTIONS  • Solid Surface Counter Top w/under Mount Country Sink • Power Awning with Shock Absorbers • LED Light Strip Porch Light • LED Power Saving Interior Lighting • Blue Tooth Stereo with DVD Player AM/FM • Night Shades in Living Area • Solar Prep for Portable Unit • Back-up Camera Prep. • Denver Pillow Top Memory Foam Mattress  ARCTIC PACKAGE (OPTIONAL)  • Radiant Foil Insulation in Roof and Floor for R-38 equivalent • Fully Enclosed Underbelly with heat duct to tank area  EXTERIOR  • Front Pass-through Storage with LED Light • Crowned Roof for Water Drainage • Black Frame Safety Glass Windows30-amp. 110v Power Cord • Cable TV Hook-up • Exterior LED Utility Porch Light • 110V Exterior Plug • Radius Entry Door with Window • Amber Step Light • Radius Compartment Storage Doors • Entry Assist Handle Main Entry • Dometic Awning w/Retractor Assist Springs • Aerodynamic Aluminum Front Cap • Omni Digital TV Antenna w/Booster • LPG Tank Cover with Easy Access • Exterior Speakers • Extended Rain Gutter Spouts • Front Lower Gravel Guard  APPLIANCES  • Suburban 3-Burner Range with 17” oven w/Stainless Steel Appliance Upgrade • Range Hood with LED Light and Exhaust Fan w/Stainless Steel Appliance Upgrade • Dometic 8-cu.ft. Stainless Steel Refrigerator • 15K BTU Ducted A/C System • 2nd A/C Prep • 8 Gal DSI 110/12V Water Heater with Bypass • Large Shower with Skylight • Toilet with Foot Flush • Queen Bed • Cold Crack Resistant Floor • Cable TV & Satellite Prep • DVD/CD/Radio Entertainment Package • Pleated Night Shades • Quad Aluminum Entry Steps • Power Bed with Convertible Sofa • Reclining Sofa Seating with Fold Down Counsel Featuring Cup Holders & USB Gravity "Apollo" Package: • Wide Body Construction • High Gloss • Aluminum Framed & Laminated Sidewalls • Tinted Safety Glass Windows • Aluminum Rims • Spare Tire • Dexter 7000# Axles • Power Front Landing Gear • Power Rear Stabilizers • Universal Docking Station with Black Tank Flush • Heated & Enclosed Underbelly • LED Stop/Turn/Tail Lights • Twin 30# LP Tanks • Exterior Speakers • Back-up Camera Prep • Power Awning with LED Light • Solar Prep • Triple Entry Garage Steps • Fuel Station with Gen Prep • Rear Ramp Door Options: • 5.5 Onan Gas Generator • Ramp Door Patio With Quick Connect Patio System • 50' Living Room TV • Electric 6 Point Leveling • 2nd 13.5K BTU Air Conditioner  Unmatched Quality Control! At Heartland, we do our absolute best to provide the best to our customers at every turn. We have integrated comprehensive testing and quality control standards throughout the production process. With our new audit facility, we're taking yet another step to ensure that your new RV is ready for camping when you tow it off the dealer lot. We also gather customer feedback through shows, plant tours, phone calls, e-mails, owners forum, rallies and letters. Heartland RV's goal is to set the standard in quality.  HOME OF THE WARRANTY FOREVER!!!  Remember all our inventory is NON AUCTION bought!  We have fought the fight in the 7 western states for you to find the cleanest pre-owned RV's and brought them to one spot, HERE!  Located at: 1444 First St. Escalon, CA 95320 ( Google Maps & Navigations will have the street as 1st ).  Open daily Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm and closed Sunday & Mondays  ****NONE OF OUR INVENTORY IS BOUGHT AT AUCTIONS!!!!  WE TAKE PRIDE IN FINDING THE CLEANEST RV’S AT UNBEATABLE PRICES!!****  We are a family owned and run business that prides itself on a “no haggle / no high pressure sales” atmosphere and that becomes obvious the moment you visit our location, no matter if you buy from us or not we appreciate you taking the time to come out and see us!  We will make you feel at home while you are in perfect company of fellow RVers and campers, as all of us also enjoy the adventures of RVing!  Make sure to check out our website for more pictures and tour video!  Our dealership main number is (209) 404-2200 and our office hours are Tuesday – Saturday 9am – 5pm and Sunday 11am-4pm,  we look forward to meeting you!  **Referral Auto Group has made every effort to ensure accuracy in the information provided, IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BUYER TO VERIFY PRIOR TO PURCHASE. ALL TRAILERS MUST BE DELIVERED AS THEY COME STRAIGHT FROM THE FACTORY TO YOUR FRONT DOOR 15% DEPOSIT REQUIRED     There are several uses for a utility trailer. Here is a glimpse at just the top ten uses of utility trailers:  1.Automobiles: From time to time it becomes necessary to haul an inoperable car or truck. Tow trucks are expensive, especially if the distance is great. A utility trailer is a great way to haul vehicles and a good investment if you need to do so regularly.  2.Boats: If you have a boat, you will need a utility trailer to get it to and from the water.  3.Lawn Care Equipment: If you live in a rural area, you may find that you need to haul your mowing equipment from one piece of your property to another. Packing equipment and loading it into a pickup truck bed can get old very quickly. A utility trailer will allow you to drive your equipment right up onto the trailer without the aid of ramps or two strong men.  4.Furniture: Moving furniture is a breeze with a utility trailer. Furniture dollies roll right up onto the trailer and you can haul more than you can with a pickup.  5.Building Supplies: Do you have projects that need to be done around the house? Pick up your own building supplies and save on delivery fees.  6.Bikes, Motorcycles, and ATVs: Recreational vehicles are best hauled on a utility trailer.  7.Livestock: An enclosed utility trailer is most often used to haul livestock.  8.Auction and Flea Markets: If you frequent auctions and flea markets, you will need the hauling capability to bring home your inexpensive and rare finds.  9.Appliances: Utility trailers are ideal for hauling appliances.  10.Debris and Trash: Loading trash in and out of your pickup bed can be cumbersome and clean up can be messy, but it would be worse to have to haul trash in your SUV. Clean up after a big job is a lot easier with a utility trailer.  As you can see, there are many reasons why an investment in a utility trailer is a smart move. I'm sure that with a little time, and its easy availability, you will come up with even more ways to use a trailer  ATV UTV SXS MOTORCYCLE BIKE TRANSPORT HAUL MOVE CAR TRUCK MOVING TRAVELING STORAGE Title: Husqvarna FE501s
text: New Husky FE501s purchased in February. Life reared it’s ugly head and I have to sell it.   Bike has been set up for enduro riding, list of upgrades includes:  -Best Enduro Bikes tuner -High Flow fuel filter  -High Flow 90o gas tank fitting -High Flow fuel rail -Best Enduro Bikes spark arrestor end cap -Grunt exhaust manifold  -Pirelli Scorpion tires -Bullet Proof blue radiator braces -blue bar ends -blue Tri Metal 50t chainring.   Bike can be completely returned to stock. None of the OE equipment was cut off, all removed the correct way. I have all the removed equipment. No smog equipment has been removed and the bike is street legal and currently registered in CA. Bike has 37 miles on it.   I am FIRM on the price, if you’re interested in the bike you know why. Thanks for taking the time to read this ad.

Title: 1998 YAMAHA YZ 250 PROJECT
text: I think I should hold the record for the most longest, boring Craigslist ad ever to be posted in the world !!!! Who agrees with me ?  IF I WERE TO GET LIKE 20 PEOPLE ALL WANTING the expensive PARTS, all at once, THIS BUILD WOULD BE PARTED OUT!  Just added up the total spent, with the 2 parts NOT in the parts listing,also just spent $30 on some EBAY decals for the bike,  total came to $4400.00 and I have it listed at just $2,000!! Crap! I could of purchased a running bike on C R A I G S L I S T at that price! Darn Madera nurse! I wish I would of have not listen to her when she told me to put my brain to work and do something I love doing!!!!  Low on funds, so the reason why I cannot finish this project, buy the coolant, oil up the air filter, change the motor oil, get the gas and pre-mix oil ETC.   TEXT FIVE-HUNDRED-FIFTY NINE-SEVEN-TEN-FOUR THREE-FOUR-ZERO if interested in purchasing my build at $2,000 FIRM.  1998 YAMAHA YZ 250 PROJECT! E B A Y BUILD! Project has not yet been started by me, needs fluids. All parts have been purchased from E B A Y and ROCKY MOUNTAIN OEM/ ATV. I have over the listed price in parts, including shipping, so FIRM on price! Seller of the frame went and had the frame powder coated after sand blasting it, so the V I N # I cannot see! I looked on the internet and there said the V I N could be found on the frame under the engine somewhere! I was like, "0000PS" but didn't locate it. But this was after the motor was installed into the frame. He stated to me that it is as clear as day to read. I have the sellers name and telephone # , just tried hunting for it, couldn't find it. Good news! I just found it! Strange how on this slip, it states 30 lbs. The motor should weigh more, Im guessing, maybe not! So should the frame and SUB frame he shipped to me. Frame and SUB is all metal, not aluminum! I will probably be the one that will be writing up a Bill of Sale as you will be purchasing this bike from me, not him. I need this project out of my bedroom ! I will show you on my old cellphone, if it can power up still and I can go back on my E B A Y 's buying page, but probably not though as the thing broke, and service is shut off, so the reason why I took the photos from the old phone with this new one, all the parts l bought and the total I put into this build to show you I am taking a huge loss on the price! I have the parts written down and the total, so you're just going to have to believe me. I am disabled from a stroke so my mind and damaged brain is not capable of allowing me to return back to riding dirt bikes safely anymore, something I have been doing since I was like 4 years old, maybe 5 or 6. just turned 51 on February the 5th. Lord I'm old !  Text 23 hours a day at FIVE-HUNDRED- FIFTY -NINE-SEVEN-TEN-FOUR -3-FOUR-ZERO if interested. Clutch cable needs to be hooked up, the rear wheel when l tighten down the axle nut, makes the rear wheel not spin OK. I might have the wheel spacers on the wrong side! I will include the bolt and nut kit I bought to install parts with, but most items on E B A Y, used parts, the seller includes them fasteners as they are parting out their bikes, and there is really nothing else to add to this build as it is complete. Pictures show the bike as I was building it, but it will roll under her own parts. Stupid me, what I should of done was snap a photo of the bare frame, and everytime a part was added to it, take a picture. I do know the motor went into the frame first, that was a job for this disabled male with a broken arm, well the arm was broken in the dirt bike crash, during the stroke, and still it feels as though there is a cast still on it that is squeezing the arm. Also it feels like someone is squeezing my hand right now. I rolled up 2 towels and placed them across the lower part of the frame , to protect the finish , then placed the motor on the 2 towels, then started to get the engine bolts and top mounting bracket installed. Dealerships has their way on which side the bolt goes through the hole and what side they place the nut on. I didn't strip this bike down,, so?? Then came the triple clamps, the old grease was completely wiped off of the steering headset bearings, lots of fresh grease was placed on those bearing roller things, AND I even got a small flat blade screwdriver and gently turned each roller and used the flat blade and forced grease into each cavity. Almost used the whole tube at that location. Also the swingarm bearings, under neath them black dust caps, got a wipe down and grease placed under there, too. I've taken apart a 1985 XR600 that I had that frame powder coated, and l got to restore that bike my way. Frame was powdercoated white, l found a swingarm on E B A Y that was powder coated the frame's orange color, had blue brand new PRO-LINK decals on it, I did 100% all new plastics, including a brand new tank, tank cost me $350 at the dealership, sold that build for a cheap $500. Stupid me!"  Then, I can't remember if the forks went on next, or was it the radiators, tank, shrouds, and I built it that way. Stupid stroke. Also, in building the sub frame, it all had to be disassembled to get all of them fasteners to bolt up. Picture shows it as 1 piece with the airbox, side panels, spark arrestor, ETC The seat was just placed on the sub frame, That was a job for this disabled male here with his damaged brain and a non usable arm and hand. . After the motor was mated to the frame, I lifted the frame with motor attached, boy was it already heavy, onto the blue plastic city's recycling bin you see in a few photos. After awhile, that blue bin started to slowly give way, so I had to get the metal stand, yep, also from E B A Y. What was funny when that stand arrived, I simply just pulled it out of its shipping box, and it was ready for usage. As with me kidding around, I emailed the place that sold the stand to me, saying, " I'm not particularly fond of my purchased item from you not having to be assembled when I removed it from its box" as a joke I sent that message! They gave me like a $8 refund! I was joking with them ! Still, some people like to make their customers happy! Will I be including the stand upon someone buying this dirt bike from me? Probably not as I have other bikes here at the house that this stand could be used for. And since this stand can slide easily on carpet, the next bike build will need to be placed on it, whenever that day comes. Also with the loss I am already taking, no need to be adding to it. Will let it go for an additional $60.  Anyways:  The seller of the motor and frame included the foot pegs, just was being a jerk and only sent me 1 foot peg spring, but I think he went and sabotaged the pegs, as on the part that your boot touches, them spikes,, all of them spikes around the edge of the pegs,, looks as though they were all filed down recently, so do NOT wear good expensive boots while riding with these foot pegs. Nice aftermarkets can be found on E B A Y, stocks also. Seller was an a$$ hole to me during the bidding process as I asked him to send a Bill of Sale with the frame, and any hole on the frame, to insert the correct fastener in it, so that I know something needs to be bolted in that hole. Like where the coil bolts onto, he could of put back the correct bolts in those holes as he included the coil. Also, the top end job he stated was done, he could of included a receipt. Dont ask me what all was done as he didn't send any paperwork with this motor. A compression check will need to be done. if this motor is even good, I am taking a huge gamble on this mystery motor. Still these parts aren't like toilet paper, an item that all people use everyday, so parting her / him out would be a slow process.  Help out a poor disabled man and take on this year's summer project, bike is a project. Looks like a dirt bike! The suspension has not yet been tested, so hopefully the fork seals are great and the rear shock isn't blown. Forks were only purchased at a price of just $60, then the $40 for shipping, the sales tax brought it up to the price listed in the parts list. Forks cost me less than the rear shock ?????????????????  THANK YOU FOR reading this far!  UPDATE: I switched the wheel spacers around, rear wheel spins better now! Maybe install a new chain and see what that does? Wheel bearings? Clutch cable attached! Routed correctly? Questionable! I still need to tighten down the front sprocket, the shift pedal, as well as the kickstarter, as we all like those certain items at a specific spot on them shafts, to get your boot under the shifter, where to correctly place the starter on the shaft, install the fluids, get some gas and change the blood, ( motor oil) and keep my fingers crossed the bike fires up! I know the clutch and throttle cables will probably need to be adjusted better, but I'm only a novice in doing stuff like that, l know front brakes work great, and the rear has a low brake pedal, will work, but you got to really push the pedal to the carpet! Bike has NOT left the bedroom since it was put together, so the tires has only touched the bedroom carpet! OOOOOPS, bike is on its E B A Y bought stand, and the front tire is on a piece of cardboard. Maybe I'm just a damaged weakling? The brake reservoir is full, I'm an old school guy, all my dirt bikes were rear drum brakes so maybe this is acceptable? I don't know. I do know on my rear drum brake bikes, my boot would rest on the foot peg, as well as the rear brake pedal, causing it to activate when riding, so what I would do is, back off a little on the rear brake adjustment. Saved on rear brake shoes this way. So maybe the really far down to push the rear brakes to the dirt, is this way of not riding the rear brakes?? Rear brake assemblies can be found on E B A Y should you need to replace the set up.  Reason for the front fender being black is, with the black powder coated swingarm, I wanted to go with a blue, black and white appearance as much as possible, so the blue and black seat. We all know what happens to blue plastics after a crash! Yep! Those white stress marks show up. The rear fender has a white stress dot on it. My father's K L X 140, yes he is that short of a guy,, had a white rear fender, as well as a green front fender. I know Honda on a XR 600, like the 1988 year, used a red rear fender and a white front fender. Or vise versa. Also with this bike being assembled in pieces, the blue gas tank doesn't match the blue radiator shrouds, as these parts was purchased from different sellers off of different bikes! Hence, the reason for no tank decals on the tank. I thought about purchasing a black fuel tank, but we all know how hard it is to see the fuel level with black fuel tanks! Trust me on that. Also black parts are hard to see, so the reason I went with the white radiator guards and the white radiator hoses. You can see them better. Now I see a white air box on E B A Y. NOPE, too expensive and I am low on funds. I won't be switching out no more parts! This is my build, I built it up my way. LOL The rear fender, the radiator shrouds, and the brand new front disc brake guard all share the same shade of blue. Tank doesn't match these parts! Let's keep that a secret between buyer and builder.  Carb is supposed to be brand spanking new, a E B A Y purchased part, so hopefully no adjustment there is needed as at the carb, things will need to be removed in order to gain access there! Just hopefully the electrical is OK and the bike fires up one day ! I placed an ad on C R A I G S awhile ago asking if the powder coating under neath where the coil bolts to, do I have to go back and scrape off the paint,, for a better ground,, and so I outlined the coil and slowly had to scrape away the nice paint job! You will never see it. Seller of the motor and frame is the same guy. He included the wiring harness, the CDI, the coil, and even had a clean spark plug in the head that looked brand spanking new. Stupid me forgot to check the # on the spark plug to see if it is correct for this motor, so that is something you will want to do before actually starting her up, and also, to check the gap. Don't want the top of the piston hitting a too long of a spark plug now! 0UCH! I ran the shifter through the gears and they are engaging, will operate the kickstarter someday.  Thank you for reading this far, hope I haven't bored you too bad ! But please continue to be bored. L0L Just please don't send me a bill for wasting your time.  Again, for those that cannot read, I'M NOT TAKING ANYMORE OF A LOSS ON THE PRICE AS I AM DOING AT $2000 ! $1995 WON'T buy the bike! $1999 WON'T even! I was offered $1200 by a person by text message that didn't read the whole ad, came back with a $1300 for his final offer by text. Yes, any amount over the listed price will be greatly appreciated. LOL I know if I had this build running and registered, it would probably sell quicker, as it will be an all year long green sticker bike. Buy this bike and part him / her out on E B A Y and make yourself a few bucks! I won't mind.  To help you guys out, prices are what I paid on E B A Y, including shipping, if the seller charged for shipping. Some items were the buy it now feature with free shipping, and some were the make offer, but now E B A Y is charging sales tax on auctions, just another way us citizens are getting ripped off in this world. If I remember correctly, I do believe the engine and the motor was the only 2 E B A Y listing that were actual auctions, the others were all buy it nows, and make offers. I'm pretty sure I made offers on all make offer auctions. Some items, I paid too much for. On the frame,, I got it at the starting bid,, as no one else in the world needed a 1998 YZ 250 bare frame last year. The motor, I'm guessing the seller had his buddies bid up the auction, and when it got around to what he wanted for it, they all stopped bidding. I think I got it for around $950 then the tax and shipping charges!  Here goes.  PARTS LIST :  MOTOR $$1149.65 FORKS $104.85 REAR SHOCK $81.19 AIR BOX $16.24 CARBURETOR $54.30 new THROTTLE $24.84. new FRONT FENDER $30.30 REAR FENDER $50.86 SEAT $89.94 R BRAKE LINE HOSE CLAMPS $13.15 those white plastic C ' s holding rear brake line onto swingarm FRAME and SUB FRAME $343.49 TRIPLE CLAMPS $106.59 FORK GUARDS 45.30 RADIATOR HOSES $ 23.80 RADIATOR SHROUDS 54.10 RADIATORS $67.10 3 # PLATES $30.00 # 61 RADIATOR LOUVERS $37.89 FRONT SPROCKET ASSEMBLY $ 18.09 REAR AXLE ASSEMBLY $45.22 FRONT CHAIN GUARD $ 17.94 FUEL / GAS TANK $317.21 FMF HEADER PIPE 301.04 MISC FRAME RUBBER $15.01 what's under the fuel tank FOOT PEG SPRINGS $10.77 AIR BOX MUD FLAP $13.80 THE 3 SPRINGS for HEADER PIPE $12.99 CHAIN ( MISC ) $39.13 SPARK ARRESTOR $92.00 C D I RUBBER BOOT $ 20.36 MUFFLER BRACKET TOP $ 38.92 Brand new MUFFLER BRACKET BOTTOM $32.42 Brand new BRAND NEW GRIPS $7.97 HANDLEBARS $81.18 SHIFT PEDAL $ 19.87 BRAND NEW AIR FILTER $28.15 INTAKE CLAMP $22.90 REAR CHAIN GUARD $41.37 SWING ARM LINKAGE $37.88 FRONT BRAKE DISC GUARD $ 30.78 the new blue piece SWING ARM $ 144.06 SWING ARM DECALS $17.52 HANDLE BAR PAD $10.83 AIR FILTER HOLD DOWN BOLT $ 8.41 WHEEL SET $423.96 CLUTCH CABLE and LEVER WITH PERCH $ 29.55 FRONT BRAKE ASSEMBLY $81.19 REAR BRAKE ASSEMBLY $64.84 TRIPLE CLAMPS FRONT BRAKE HOLD DOWN METAL BRACKET $19.12  PLUS 3 ORDERS PLACED AT ROCKY MOUNTAIN OEM / ATV for bolts, nuts ETC totalling almost $400. I know the rear shock was just $75 with free shipping, the tax brought the price up to the listed amount. I can't believe I paid more for the fuel tank, than I did for the FMF header pipe!  And any remaining parts I forgot, like the brand new kill switch, and the fuel tank's breather tube, I'm not going to post , so firm on price at $2,000. The reason for the #61, those were purchased on E B A Y and that was the number. You may change it to whatever # you prefer. I'm just glad it wasn't # 69 ! Would of made me look like I was the pervert! L0L In 10 more years , 61 will be my age!  Grips and the air filter are probably the only items that are brand new! 000PS, the seller of the header pipe states the pipe was NEVER used, OH and the carb is supposed to be new, the air box mounted mud flap / guard is brand new, and the throttle plastic and housing are new E B A Y items! Would like for this project to go to someone that will finally get her to the trail someday! I will use the funds from this sale and start up another project, or maybe not! Need to support my Starbucks addiction! With me not selling this build, maybe I will get the radiator coolant, the gas and oil mixture, oil up the air filter, get her fresh oil and see if my build is a YAAAAA ! or a NAAAAA!  How my dirt bike building hobby began was, a long time ago, on E B A Y there was a 1984 YZ 80 being parted out. I wanted to turn the fuel tank into a unique piggy bank. Cut slots in the top to accept the coins. You just simply turn the thing upside down after unscrewing the fuel tank cap to get the coins to dump out. Well anyways, the fuel tank was all complete, nice, petcock, mounting brackets, nice stock fuel tank decals ETC, and sold for a great price! The tank arrived, a light bulb went off in my head, saying to me, I cannot afford to buy a dirtbike outright, why not build it piece by piece? And so the dirt bike building days began. I felt sorry for the 1 guy selling the 85 YZ 80 frame on E B A Y as it only sold for $10 with free shipping. I built the bike, a red 85 frame, 84 yellow plastics, a black seat, and a front disc brake set up, where as a stock 85 is supposed to be drums in the front. I bought a 1984 YZ80 from a high school classmate of mine for just $300. My parents bought me a brand spanking new 1985 YZ80 that was only $1200 off the showroom floor, or out the door,, and even included a spark arrestor!! Oh the cheap prices way back then ! With the extra parts I was getting with building the 1985, I constructed a YZ 80 with a white frame, so let's call him a 1990. The 85 I was able to get running, the 1990, I wasn't so lucky. And stupid me never attempted to diagnose why that 1 wouldnt start, I started parted it out on C R A I G S L I S T, and got the motor sold on E B A Y as a non running motor! Then came K B F L A T F A C E from E B A Y. I guess it is a parting out place on the east coast. There I bought a 1986 Honda Z50R-D frame, forks, swingarm, exhaust pipe, and handlebars from him. The fenders, seat, rear shocks, and fuel tank were all brand new reproduction parts, the motor and wheels were from a Honda Z50R, just not correct for 1986 as they were supposed to be chrome parts. I never attempted or tried to get the Honda running, added up what I put into the build, total came to like $1500. I placed the ad on C R A I G S L I S T, got the bike sold to a gentleman living in Pleasanton! The 1985 that I built, later I saw it reposted on CL, the seat cover was all torn up, ripped, and thrashed, I paid like $25 for the seat on E B A Y. So I can honestly say I built 4 bikes all from E B A Y auctions. Just 3 are, or should be still built. Hopefully 1 day this YZ 250 sells.  The End, hopefully !  Reason why this ad doesn't make since is, I would go back and add to it, because of the stroke I suffered, I dont remember things right away, and so the reason for the carb being listed as brand new a few times. In staring at the fuel tanks cap new breather tube that just arrived yesterday, Valentine's Day, the hose looks as though it is too long and should be shortened by an inch. Will let the new owner decide on that. It's 3" from top of fuel cap to bottom of the nice color cap breather part on top of the hose.  OK, the end! Definitely!!

The bike seat and handles adjust to your size (56-74" tall).  Purchased on Amazon so I just cut and pasted the info that had me purchasing it, and I really like the easy set up those few times needed before I got the tow vehicle.   Very nice.  Take a good look at the pictures I have -some from Amazon.com and some of my own.  The information on Amazon seems very precise even 3 years later.  I find it very easy to fold up and unfold and light enough to carry.  It would fit easily in your car trunk.
